    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-22T19:23:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-22T19:23:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/3–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 443<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d443fn1">Repeated to Tehran and Paris. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SJH1">Stutesman</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_JJD1"
                            >Jernegan</persName> and approved by <persName corresp="#p_BHA1"
                            >Byroade</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-03-22T19:23:00-05:00"
                            >March 22, 1954—7:23 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4885. Limited distribution. For <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>.
                    Although recognizing importance British ascribe to matter, Dept cannot agree to
                    support figure 100 million pounds suggested by UK Govt as compensation by Iran
                    to <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss>. Arguments put forward by <gloss
                        target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName> (Tehran tel 1977, sent London
                    604, being rptd Paris by Dept) and <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1"
                    >Hoover</persName>’s additional arguments (paras 5 and 6 London tel 4057, rptd
                    Paris 546, rptd Tehran 180) seem to us overriding and almost incontrovertible.
                    Insofar as principle of payment of compensation by Iran to <gloss
                        target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> is concerned, apart from internal
                    arrangements within consortium for payment <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss>
                    interests, Dept believes maximum which could be contemplated by Iranians would
                    be compensation for such <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> assets in Iran as
                    are not recovered under consortium contract, along lines para 4 Tehran tel
                    1977.</p>
                <p>British Embassy has presented memorandum here which states, <hi rend="italic"
                        >inter alia</hi>, that compensation must be paid by Iran because otherwise
                        <pb facs="0991" n="965" xml:id="pg_965"/> total received by <gloss
                        target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> from consortium would place too low figure on
                    value <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> enterprise in Iran. Department
                    unable concur that overall value of one billion dollars, as now agreed by
                    companies on commercial basis, is too low in view of all circumstances.</p>
                <p>Above position, expanded to include arguments used in pertinent London and Tehran
                    tels, communicated British Embassy today with statement that Secretary and
                    others in Cabinet held strong views on this subject. We now eagerly await report
                        <persName corresp="#p_AWW1">Aldrich</persName> and your meeting with
                        <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>.</p>
                <p>Re para 6 London tel 4057,<note n="2" xml:id="d443fn2">Paragraph 6 of telegram
                        4057, Mar. 21, reported that the British Government had conveyed the view
                        that the Department of State supported the principle that some compensation
                        to <gloss target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> should be paid by Iran.
                        (888.2553/3–2154)</note> informal conversation with British Embassy
                    representatives was held before receipt <persName corresp="#p_HLW1"
                        >Henderson</persName>’s views and with understanding comments conditional
                    upon Tehran’s reaction and high level study of question here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
